Let's get into scripture

As mentioned, we are moving through sermon on the mount, arguably the most powerful and famous sermon ever given

It was given by Jesus in front of thousands of people and the account we're reading was written by Matthew

Matthew is one of the 4 gospels in the new testament of the bible

Matthew was an outcast jew who abandoned his life as a tax collector for rome to become one of Jesus' closest students known as apostles

The 12 apostles spent time with Jesus and served as eyewitnesses to his teachings and interactions over the course of his ministry

Matthews account of sermon on the mount is an extremey detailed account. It spans 111 verses and around 2400 words

Although those 111 verses would only take you around 15 minutes to read end to end at an average reading pace, it is super dense and loaded with wisdom which is why we're moving through it very slowly


In chapter 5 Jesus delivers heart training





